Package lamblin.medianwordsperline

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RunningMedian<T>
    Accepts entries to calculate the median over, and returns that median.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    QueueRunningMedian<T extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Keeps track of the running median and returns it on each update of the inputs so far.
    RangeRunningMedian<T extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Updates a running median for all the data input with each update of added data.
    RunningMedianModule
    Configures the state of RunningMedianWordsPerLineCmd and its dependencies, using Module's Arguments.
    RunningMedianWordsPerLineCmd
    The Insight Data Engineering Coding Challenge issued 2015-03-17 The Java version.
    TransformingRunningMedian<T,E extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    A RunningMedian encapsulation that transforms its TransformingRunningMedian.update(T) method inputs for correct storage in the constructor parameter's provided RunningMedian implementation.
    WordCountTransformer
    Cleans the words on the lines of non-AlphaNumerics, and removes empty or all-digit words, then it counts the remaining words on that line.
